---
title: Sunny Lemon Chicken Rigatoni plus Roasted Broccoli, Parmesan & Parsley
description: Think you’ve had every possible combination of chicken and pasta? Think again—our decadent spin on “chicken riggies” is one exciting shake-up in a bowl! A bright, tangy cream sauce made with seared lemon slices and Parmesan cheese coats juicy sautéed Italian-seasoned chicken. The saucy chicken is tossed with rigatoni, then topped with charred lemon slices and fresh parsley. A side of roasted broccoli rounds out this sunny dinner idea.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/64ad6e2608c61453c499aac8-391ef93c.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/64ad6e2608c61453c499aac8.pdf
cuisine: Italian
time required: 40 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 870 kcal
  fat: 38 g
  saturated fat: 17 g
  carbohydrates: 86 g
  sugar: 10 g
  protein: 53 g
  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 800 mg
author: Michelle Doll Olson
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sunny-lemon-chicken-rigatoni-64ad6e2608c61453c499aac8
course: main course
---

Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Adjust rack to top position and preheat
oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Thinly slice one
@lemon{1} (thinly sliced) (for 4 servings, thinly slice two lemons; quarter remaining
lemons). Quarter remaining @lemon{1} (quartered) (for 4 servings, quarter two lemons).
Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Roughly chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}.

Toss broccoli on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tbsp}, @garlic powder{1%tsp},
@salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> If needed, cover broccoli with foil to keep warm until ready to serve.

Once water is boiling, add @rigatoni pasta{6%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally,
until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve 1/4 cup pasta cooking water (1/2 cup for 4
servings), then drain.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; place between 2 large pieces
of #plastic wrap{}. Pound with a #mallet{} or #rolling pin{} until chicken is about
½ inch thick. Season all over with @Italian seasoning{1%tsp} (2 tsp for 4 servings),
salt, and pepper.

> Be sure to measure the Italian Seasoning—we sent more!

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook until
brown and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan and let cool slightly.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add lemon slices in a single
layer; cook, stirring occasionally, until fragrant and lightly browned, ~{1-2%minutes}.
Transfer to a #plate{}.

Add garlic to same pan and cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Whisk in reserved pasta cooking water, @cream sauce base{4%ounce}, @chicken stock concentrate{1},
@Parmesan cheese{3%tbsp}, and juice from two lemon wedges (four wedges for 4 servings).
Cook, whisking, until slightly thickened, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Reduce heat to medium low. Whisk in @sour cream{1.5%tbsp} and @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4)
until smooth.

Slice chicken crosswise. Add chicken to pan and toss to coat.

Divide drained rigatoni between shallow #bowls{}; top with saucy chicken. Spoon any
remaining sauce from pan over everything. Garnish with seared lemon slices and parsley.

Serve with roasted broccoli and remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.